{{Merge to|lucene|date=May 2011}} '''Kinosearch''' is a [[search engine]] written in [[Perl]] and [[C (programming language)|C]]<ref name = cmswire>{{cite news |url=http://www.cmswire.com/cms/enterprise-20/socialtext-updates-search-goes-kino-001037.php |title=Socialtext Updates Search, Goes Kino |first=Angela |last=Natividad |publisher=CMS Wire|date= |accessdate=2011-05-31}}</ref> and a loose [[Porting|port]] of the Java search engine library Apache [[Lucene]].<ref name="test">[http://p3rl.org/KinoSearch#DESCRIPTION Description on [[CPAN]]]</ref>
The [[Socialtext]] wiki software uses this search engine,<ref name = cmswire /> and so does the [[MojoMojo]] wiki.<ref name="catbook">{{cite book | last = Diment | first = Kieren | coauthors = Trout, Matt S | title = The Definitive Guide to Catalyst | publisher = [[Apress]] | year = 2009 | page = 280 | chapter = Catalyst Cookbook | isbn = 978-1-4302-2365-8 }}</ref> It is also used by the [[Human Metabolome Database]] (HMDB)<ref>{{cite journal|pmc=2686599 | pmid=18953024 | doi=10.1093/nar/gkn810 | volume=37 | issue=Database issue | title=HMDB: a knowledgebase for the human metabolome | year=2009 | month=January | journal=[[Nucleic Acids Res.]] | pages=D603–10}}</ref> and the [[Toxin and Toxin-Target Database]] (T3DB).<ref>{{cite journal|pmc=2808899 | pmid=19897546 | doi=10.1093/nar/gkp934 | volume=38 | issue=Database issue | title=T3DB: a comprehensively annotated database of common toxins and their targets | year=2010 | month=January | journal=Nucleic Acids Res. | pages=D781–6}}</ref>
[[Apache Lucy]] is a successor project of KinoSeach and [[Ferret search library]], being jointly developed by the authors of these, and having bindings in both [[Perl]] and [[Ruby (programming language)|Ruby]].<ref>{{cite book|author1=Michael McCandless|author2=Erik Hatcher|author3=Otis Gospodnetić|title=Lucene in Action|year=2010|publisher=[[Manning Publications]]|isbn=978-1-933988-17-7|url=http://my.safaribooksonline.com/book/web-development/seo/9781933988177|page=338|edition=2}}</ref><ref>http://lucene.apache.org/lucy</ref>
